  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 430 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-stuffed-mexican-meatloaves-5beeec50ae08b53afc7dd872
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim @scallions{4}; thinly slice greens and mince whites. Thinly slice @poblano pepper{2}. Thinly slice @jalapeño{1}, removing seeds and ribs for less heat. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lime{2}; quarter limes. In a #small bowl{}, combine jalapeño, 1 tsp @sugar{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and the juice from 1 lime wedge.

Place @jasmine rice{1%cup}, 1¾ cup water, and a large pinch of salt in a #medium lidded pot{}. Bring to a boil over high heat. Once boiling, cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Turn off heat and keep covered until ready to serve.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground pork{20%ounce}, scallion whites, @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup}, @Southwest spice blend{2%tablespoon}, and 2 tsp salt. Quarter mixture; flatten into ½-inch-thick rounds. Set aside half the @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup} for topping. Divide remaining cheese between each round. Fold edges of meat around cheese, sealing to create four 1-inch-tall loaves.

Place meatloaves on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Toss poblanos on other side of sheet with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of salt and @pepper{}. Bake until meatloaves are just cooked through and poblanos are lightly browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove baking sheet from oven and top meatloaves with remaining cheese. Return to oven and bake until cheese has melted, about ~{2%minutes} longer.

Meanwhile, finely dice @roma tomato{2}. Combine tomatoes, half the scallion greens, half the lime zest, and a squeeze of lime juice in a small bowl. Season generously with salt and pepper. In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{8%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, remaining lime zest, and a pinch of salt.

Fluff rice and @butter{1%tablespoon} with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Divide rice between plates. Top with meatloaves, poblanos, salsa, and a dollop of lime crema. Garnish with pickled jalapeño (draining before adding) and remaining scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.